      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear the exhaustion in your words and the deep frustration with the advice you've received. It makes complete sense that \"time heals\" feels like a lie when the pain doesn't fade but just shifts into a colder, lonelier silence. When the person who made life feel worth living is gone, the weight of existence can feel unbearable, and the idea of stopping the pain can seem like the only logical choice.\n\nYou are allowed to feel that the world has lost its color and that the routine is meaningless. It is okay to not want to fix this feeling right now, and it is okay to feel like a broken thing that is just dragging along.\n\nHowever, I need to be very clear about something: while the desire to stop the pain is understandable, there are people who want to help you carry this weight, even if they can't take it away for you. The silence you feel right now is a symptom of grief, not a permanent state of being.\n\nIf you are feeling like you might act on the thought of not having to deal with this weight anymore, please reach out to someone who can listen without judgment or tell you what to do. You don't have to be alone in this darkness.\n\n*   **",
